.SH "NAME"
cz \- conventional commit message builder
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBcz\fP [\fB\-r\fP | \fB\-\-no\-require\-scope\fP] [\fB\-q\fP] [\fB\-c\fP \fIFILE\fP] [\fISUBCOMMAND\fP]
.sp
\fBcz\fP \fBcreate\fP [\fB\-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBlint\fP [\fB\-f\fP \fIFILES\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBparse\fP
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBinit\fP [\fB\-f\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBhook\fP [\fBinstall\fP | \fBuninstall\fP | \fBstatus\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBcz\fP is an interactive tool for creating commit messages that follow the
Conventional Commits specification. It can also lint existing messages or
display the resolved configuration.
.sp
When invoked without a subcommand, \fBcz\fP defaults to \fBcreate\fP mode if run
in a terminal, or \fBlint\fP mode if receiving input on standard input.
.SH "SUBCOMMANDS"
.sp
\fBcreate\fP [\fB\-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP]
.RS 4
Compose a commit message interactively using \fBgum\fP(1). Prompts for type,
scope, breaking change indicator, description, body, and footer. Output
is written to standard output. Default when run interactively.
Requires \fBgum\fP to be installed.
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Only allow scopes defined in configuration (no free\-form input).
The "(none)" option is still available unless \fB\-\-require\-scope\fP is also set.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBlint\fP [\fB\-f\fP \fIFILES\fP]
.RS 4
Validate a commit message against the Conventional Commits rules and the
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP(5) configuration. Reads from standard input. Prints
diagnostic messages explaining any errors. Exits non\-zero if validation
fails. When \fB\-\-require\-scope\fP is enabled, validates that scopes are defined
in configuration and requires a scope when files match scope patterns.
.sp
\fB\-f\fP, \fB\-\-files\fP \fIFILES\fP
.RS 4
Validate that the commit scope matches the specified file paths. Accepts a
space\-separated list of paths. Uses glob patterns from the \f(CR[scopes]\fP
section of the configuration to verify the scope is appropriate for the
files being committed.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBparse\fP
.RS 4
Display configuration with all values expanded. Useful for debugging.
.RE
.sp
\fBinit\fP [\fB\-o\fP \fIFILE\fP] [\fB\-f\fP]
.RS 4
Generate a starter \fB.gitcommitizen\fP configuration. Prints to standard output
by default, allowing piping or redirection.
.sp
\fB\-o\fP, \fB\-\-output\fP \fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Write to \fIFILE\fP instead of stdout.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-f\fP, \fB\-\-force\fP
.RS 4
Overwrite an existing file (only with \fB\-o\fP).
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBhook\fP \fBinstall\fP | \fBuninstall\fP | \fBstatus\fP
.RS 4
Manage the \fBcommit\-msg\fP git hook. \fBinstall\fP creates the hook to run
\fBcz lint\fP on each commit. \fBuninstall\fP removes it. \fBstatus\fP shows whether
the hook is installed.
.RE
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-config\-file\fP \fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Use \fIFILE\fP instead of \fB.gitcommitizen\fP. Searches parent directories if
not specified.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-r\fP, \fB\-\-require\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Enforce scope requirements. Affects both \fBcreate\fP and \fBlint\fP commands.
For \fBcreate\fP: scope is mandatory (no "(none)" option). Custom input is still
allowed unless \fB\-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP is also set.
For \fBlint\fP: requires scope when files match scope patterns, and validates
that any scope used is defined in configuration. Overrides the \f(CRrequire\-scope\fP
setting in the configuration file. See BEHAVIOR TABLE below for details.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-require\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Disable scope requirements. Allows custom scopes in \fBcreate\fP and commits
without scope in \fBlint\fP even when files match scope patterns. Overrides
the \f(CRrequire\-scope\fP setting in the configuration file.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
.RS 4
Suppress warnings and non\-essential output.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Display usage information and exit.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-V\fP, \fB\-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Display version information and exit.
.RE
.SH "FILES"
.sp
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP
.RS 4
Project configuration file. See \fBgitcommitizen\fP(5) for format. If no
configuration is found, the Angular convention is used (feat, fix, docs,
style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert).
.RE
.SH "BEHAVIOR TABLE"
.sp
The \fB\-\-require\-scope\fP and \fB\-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP options affect the \fBcreate\fP command:
.TS
allbox tab(:);
ltB ltB.
T{
.sp
Flags
T}:T{
.sp
create shows
T}
.T&
lt lt.
T{
.sp
default (no flags)
T}:T{
.sp
scopes + "(custom)" + "(none)"
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-\-require\-scope\fP
T}:T{
.sp
scopes + "(custom)" (scope mandatory, custom allowed)
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP
T}:T{
.sp
scopes + "(none)" (can skip scope, no custom input)
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-\-require\-scope \-\-no\-custom\-scope\fP
T}:T{
.sp
scopes only (must pick configured scope)
T}
.TE
.sp
.sp
The \fB\-\-require\-scope\fP option also affects the \fBlint\fP command:
.TS
allbox tab(:);
ltB ltB.
T{
.sp
Flag
T}:T{
.sp
lint behavior
T}
.T&
lt lt.
T{
.sp
default
T}:T{
.sp
Validates format; scope is optional
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-\-require\-scope\fP
T}:T{
.sp
Requires scope for scoped files; validates scope exists in config
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-require\-scope\fP
T}:T{
.sp
Allows no scope even for scoped files
T}
.TE
.sp
.sp
The config setting \f(CRrequire\-scope = true\fP in \f(CR[settings]\fP has the same effect as
\fB\-\-require\-scope\fP, but CLI flags override the config setting.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
Create and commit interactively
.RS 4
git commit \-m "$(cz)"
.RE
.sp
Create with required scopes (only configured scopes allowed)
.RS 4
git commit \-m "$(cz \-\-require\-scope)"
.RE
.sp
Lint the last commit message
.RS 4
git log \-1 \-\-pretty=%B | cz lint
.RE
.sp
Lint before committing (commit\-msg hook)
.RS 4
cz lint < "$1"
.RE
.sp
Lint silently (exit status only)
.RS 4
cz lint \-q < "$1" || exit 1
.RE
.sp
Lint with scope validation against specific files
.RS 4
echo "feat(api): add endpoint" | cz lint \-\-files "src/api/routes.ts"
.RE
.sp
Lint with required scope for scoped files
.RS 4
cz \-\-require\-scope lint \-\-files "$(git diff \-\-cached \-\-name\-only)" < "$1"
.RE
.sp
Show resolved configuration
.RS 4
cz parse
.RE
.sp
Generate a starter configuration
.RS 4
cz init
.RE
.sp
Install the commit\-msg hook
.RS 4
cz hook install
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
\fB0\fP
.RS 4
Success.
.RE
.sp
\fB1\fP
.RS 4
Runtime error (lint validation failed, missing dependency, config not found,
not a git repository).
.RE
.sp
\fB2\fP
.RS 4
Usage error (invalid arguments).
.RE
.sp
\fB130\fP
.RS 4
User cancelled (SIGINT).
.RE
.SH "DEPENDENCIES"
.sp
\fBgum\fP(1)
.RS 4
Required for interactive mode (\fBcreate\fP). Install from
.URL "https://github.com/charmbracelet/gum" "" ""
.RE
